-- Abu Dhabi’s Mubadala in $1 Billion Investment in Russia
-- B y   I l y a   A r k h i p o v
-- 2013-06-20T19:59:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-20/abu-dhabi-s-mubadala-development-to-invest-1-billion-in-russia.html
Mubadala Development Co., owned by
 Abu Dhabi ’s government, agreed to contribute half of a $2
billion investment fund it’s setting up with the Russian Direct
Investment Fund.  The fund will focus on a “range of industry sectors” and
“is aligned with Mubadala’s plans to establish a strong
presence in key international markets,” Mubadala Chief
Executive Officer Khaldoon Al Mubarak and his RDIF counterpart
Kirill Dmitriev said in a joint statement distributed today near
St. Petersburg.  The RDIF is also planning an infrastructure fund with
Macquarie Group Ltd., Australia’s largest investment bank,
Dmitriev said during a meeting with President  Vladimir Putin .  Industries of interest for cooperation with foreign funds
include road building, railways and telecommunications, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Arkhipov in Moscow at 
